rComments: Exams are based solely on the textbook. She never seems ready for her lectures, she has to look at her notes between slides (for like 30 seconds-1 minutes) which makes the lectures boring.

She wasn't very clear during lectures. She obviously knows her stuff but doesn't know how to teach it. I remember one of our exams, students were pissed because she put stuff she didn't even teach. Her defence was: "i know it was a hard exam".

Cette enseignante est très confuse et le cours est très long. Elle ne donne aucune pause pour un cours de 3 heures. Elle est très gentille, mais son enseignement 'est vraiment pas adéquat, lecture de ses power points, difficulté à donner des explications.

Ses cours sont très long puisqu'elle ne fait que lire ses powerpoint (qui sont inutiles), et elle n'explique pas vraiment la matière. Ses réponses aux questions ne sont pas très claires. Elle semble très confuse, ce qui rends l'apprentissage difficile. Lire les chapitres du livre et bien étudier la matière est plus utile que d'aller au cour.
The teaching for this class was extremely boring.

She questions herself constantly and assumes that because she understands the material, we will too. She reads her notes before explaining the slide, which makes the lecture boring. Her explanations aren't clear and although her exams are multiple choice, the questions aren't always clear. I would not recommend taking this class if she's your prof.

Probably the worst teacher I've ever had by far. She really isn't clear when she teaches. It also seems like she has no idea what she's talking about. For example, before she starts teaching a slide, she reads notes she's written down for herself for about 2 minutes. If you can have another prof for psych, take it.
Never again! She dosen't seem sure about what she's teaching.

She's obviously very intelligent but due to her lack of experience teaching, she has lots of difficulty explaining the material. I didn't attend one class, I just read the book and the power points she gave us (which were amazing and clear). Great class to take, but lectures will be painful if she's your prof!
It seem like she doesn't know what she's teaching. The way she explains the content is very confusing.

Lectures: explains things, gets confused and then stops talking. Repeat x 1.5 hours.  Midterms: 1 concept repeated 60 times. Gets mad at people in class for talking. Or leaving. Or laughing. (Or breathing?)
She doesn't finish her trail of thoughts.. she just says "C'est ça"  She turns her back and talks to the board so you can't hear anything No point of going to class.. just read the manuel..
Really bad.  Doesn't know her stuff at all, no clue what she's teaching. Really bad teacher.

She seems to have no experience in teaching and does not seem to know her course content. She leaves many thoughts unfinished which is confusing for students. Attending her classes confuse me more than not attending.
Doesn't seem to entirely understand what she is teaching.
Needs better preparation before class... seems a bit lost and confused...
Going to class was a complete waste of my time since the prof was no help at all.
